    {
      "segments": [
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:1.1",
          "pli": "Sāvatthiyaṃ jetavane. ",
          "en": "Near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:1.2",
          "pli": "Tatra kho … pe … etadavoca: ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:1.3",
          "pli": "“bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo mātaliṃ saṅgāhakaṃ āmantesi: ",
          "en": "“Once upon a time, mendicants, Sakka, lord of gods, addressed his charioteer Mātali, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:1.4",
          "pli": "‘yojehi, samma mātali, sahassayuttaṃ ājaññarathaṃ, uyyānabhūmiṃ gacchāma subhūmiṃ dassanāyā’ti. ",
          "en": "‘My dear Mātali, harness the chariot with its team of a thousand thoroughbreds. We will go to a park and see the scenery.’ "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:1.5",
          "pli": "‘Evaṃ, bhaddantavā’ti kho, bhikkhave, mātali saṅgāhako sakkassa devānamindassa paṭissutvā, sahassayuttaṃ ājaññarathaṃ yojetvā sakkassa devānamindassa paṭivedesi: ",
          "en": "‘Yes, lord,’ replied Mātali. He harnessed the chariot and informed Sakka, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:1.6",
          "pli": "‘yutto kho te, mārisa, sahassayutto ājaññaratho, ",
          "en": "‘Good sir, the chariot with its team of a thousand thoroughbreds has been harnessed. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:1.7",
          "pli": "yassadāni kālaṃ maññasī’ti.",
          "en": "Please go at your convenience.’"
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:1.8",
          "pli": "Atha kho, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo vejayantapāsādā orohanto añjaliṃ katvā sudaṃ bhikkhusaṃghaṃ namassati. ",
          "en": "Then Sakka descended from the Palace of Victory, raised his joined palms, and revered the mendicant Saṅgha. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:1.9",
          "pli": "Atha kho, bhikkhave, mātali saṅgāhako sakkaṃ devānamindaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: ",
          "en": "So Mātali the charioteer addressed Sakka in verse: "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:2.1",
          "pli": "‘Tañhi ete namasseyyuṃ, ",
          "en": "‘It’s these who should worship you, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:2.2",
          "pli": "pūtidehasayā narā; ",
          "en": "namely the humans stuck in their putrid bodies, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:2.3",
          "pli": "Nimuggā kuṇapamhete, ",
          "en": "sunk in a corpse, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:2.4",
          "pli": "khuppipāsasamappitā. ",
          "en": "stricken by hunger and thirst. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:3.1",
          "pli": "Kiṃ nu tesaṃ pihayasi, ",
          "en": "Why then do you envy those "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:3.2",
          "pli": "anāgārāna vāsava; ",
          "en": "who are homeless, Vāsava? "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:3.3",
          "pli": "Ācāraṃ isinaṃ brūhi, ",
          "en": "Relate the hermits’ way of life, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:3.4",
          "pli": "taṃ suṇoma vaco tavā’ti. ",
          "en": "let us hear what you have to say.’ "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:4.1",
          "pli": "‘Etaṃ tesaṃ pihayāmi, ",
          "en": "‘This is why I envy the "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:4.2",
          "pli": "anāgārāna mātali; ",
          "en": "homeless, Mātali. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:4.3",
          "pli": "Yamhā gāmā pakkamanti, ",
          "en": "When they leave a village, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:4.4",
          "pli": "anapekkhā vajanti te. ",
          "en": "they go without concern. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:5.1",
          "pli": "Na tesaṃ koṭṭhe openti, ",
          "en": "They hoard no goods in storerooms, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:5.2",
          "pli": "na kumbhi na kaḷopiyaṃ; ",
          "en": "nor in pots or baskets. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:5.3",
          "pli": "Paraniṭṭhitamesānā, ",
          "en": "They seek food prepared by others, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:5.4",
          "pli": "tena yāpenti subbatā. ",
          "en": "and, true to their vows, live on that. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:6.1",
          "pli": "Sumantamantino dhīrā, ",
          "en": "The wise whose words are full of wisdom, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:6.2",
          "pli": "tuṇhībhūtā samañcarā; ",
          "en": "live peacefully and quietly. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:6.3",
          "pli": "Devā viruddhā asurehi, ",
          "en": "Gods fight with demons, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:6.4",
          "pli": "puthu maccā ca mātali. ",
          "en": "and mortals fight each other, Mātali. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:7.1",
          "pli": "Aviruddhā viruddhesu, ",
          "en": "Not fighting among those who fight, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:7.2",
          "pli": "attadaṇḍesu nibbutā; ",
          "en": "they’re extinguished among those who’ve taken up arms. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:7.3",
          "pli": "Sādānesu anādānā, ",
          "en": "Not grasping among those who grasp, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:7.4",
          "pli": "te namassāmi mātalī’ti. ",
          "en": "they’re who I worship, Mātali.’ "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:8.1",
          "pli": "‘Seṭṭhā hi kira lokasmiṃ, ",
          "en": "‘Those who you worship "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:8.2",
          "pli": "ye tvaṃ sakka namassasi; ",
          "en": "seem to be the best in the world, Sakka. "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:8.3",
          "pli": "Ahampi te namassāmi, ",
          "en": "I too will worship "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:8.4",
          "pli": "ye namassasi vāsavā’”ti. ",
          "en": "those who you worship, Vāsava.’ "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:9.1",
          "pli": "Idaṃ vatvāna maghavā, ",
          "en": "After saying this, Maghavā the chief, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:9.2",
          "pli": "devarājā sujampati; ",
          "en": "king of gods, Sujā’s husband, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:9.3",
          "pli": "Bhikkhusaṅghaṃ namassitvā, ",
          "en": "having worshipped the mendicant Saṅgha, "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:9.4",
          "pli": "pamukho rathamāruhīti. ",
          "en": "climbed into his chariot.” "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:9.5",
          "pli": "Dutiyo vaggo. ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:10.1",
          "pli": "Devā pana tayo vuttā, ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:10.2",
          "pli": "daliddañca rāmaṇeyyakaṃ; ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:10.3",
          "pli": "Yajamānañca vandanā, ",
          "en": " "
        },
        {
          "scid": "sn11.20:10.4",
          "pli": "tayo sakkanamassanāti. ",
          "en": ""
        }
      ],
